Director, e-Commerce & Strategic Alliances CEMEALocation: United Arab Emirates-Dubai-DubaiOrganization: Product ManagementJob: Product Development/ManagementJob Number : #DescriptionVisa operates the world's largest retail electronic payments network and is one of the most recognized global financial services brands. Visa facilitates global commerce through the transfer of value and information among financial institutions, merchants, consumers, businesses and government entities.We offer a range of branded payment product platforms, which our financial institution clients use to develop and offer credit, charge, deferred debit, prepaid and cash access programs to cardholders. Visa's card platforms provide consumers, businesses, merchants and government entities with a secure, convenient and reliable way to pay and be paid in 170 countries and territories.1. PurposeThe Emerging Products group has the mandate to expand Visa's operational scope beyond traditional clients and products. Ideal candidate will have the proven ability to develop a deployment plan for mobile payments and execute on Visa’s e-Commerce payments growth objectives for a geographically and culturally diverse region.Business Leadership role for e-Commerce innovation for Central Eastern Europe, Middle East & Africa (CEMEA). Integrating manager for e-Commerce products across CEMEA. Role holder is recognized as an expert within Visa. Provides technical and functional leadership on e-Commerce payments for the region. The role holder must possess an excellent blend of business, technical, and product management skills – as well as domain expertise in e-Commerce– to ensure that Visa can establish itself as a leader in these areas both amongst traditional and other non-traditional competitors to Visa.2. Principle Responsibilities/Key Results Area- Work with relevant Group Country Managers (GCMs), Country Managers (CMs) and Business Development Managers (BDMs) the role holder must make a defining contribution to business development and sales efforts for e-Commerce such as VbyV, dynamic authentication, checkout and other e-Commerce developments and enhanced VbyV solutions in market, cross-border online shopping alliances with key Clients and online merchants- Develop working level collaboration with internet payment service providers- Workshops and best practice sharing conducted in co-ordination with Risk for improved authorization performance among clients- Grow e-Commerce Acceptance through building relationships and partnerships with key sector leaders for instance, e-government for payments and utility companies.- Leverage Government relationships to the advantage of Visa E-commerce Strategy and Agenda- Develop new e-Commerce business by opening new products to internet payment e.g. Debit and Pre-Paid- Actively contribute to and lead efforts in pre-sales, sales, business case development, launch, implementation, and post-launch support- Strong collaboration and knowledge transfer of best practice between other geographic managers- Recognized expert within Visa, represent Visa to external partners on e-Commerce-related matters in CEMEA- Serve as a Visa’s e-Commerce representative at relevant conferences, industry associations, and media briefings within the geography- Demonstrable evidence of solid partnerships with key third parties- Identify, qualify and quantify market specific opportunities and understand critical factors to successful market deployment of e-Commerce payments across CEMEA- Create annual operating plan for e-Commerce payments across CEMEA. Manage e-Commerce innovation priorities and all supporting activities locally, with support from global and regional emerging products teams- Manages communications and relationships with external stakeholders including vendors, external consultants, 3rd party solution providers, merchants and technology partners to deliver e-Commerce payments initiatives- Ensures continuous monitoring of local market benchmark in terms of competitive activity and capabilities- Work directly with local market teams, clients and partners (in conjunction with global and regional solutions teams) to implement initiatives to drive the innovation agenda in-country and grow the e-Commerce payments3. Strategic Nature, Mgmt Accountability, & Scope- Business leadership role; Recognized as a e-Commerce payments expert within Visa- Specialized e-Commerce expertise to lead mobile payments transactions across CEMEA- Influences the e-Commerce payments strategy to address internal, external and regulatory issues- Contributes to the development of e-Commerce strategy, provides e-Commerce leadership and ensures the implementation of annual e-Commerce goals & plans- Provides leadership to managers and other professional staff, leads e-Commerce projects and manages products without direct reports4. Decision Making & Complexity- Responsibility for execution and effective planning of annual e-Commerce, budget- Presentation and recommendations relating to potential, investment, projects, partnerships and initiatives Visa may undertake- Accurate reporting to clients- Decisions impact the implementation of e-Commerce plans to achieve EPI annual goals- Develops e-Commerce plans including business and organizational priorities- Contributes to the development of e-Commerce strategy and recommends product or service improvements- Operates with limited guidance in a complex environment and broad geographies5. Financial & Organizational Scope- CEMEA e-Commerce numbers6. Reporting Relationships & Interactions- Individual contributor- Role holder is based in the Dubai office, reports to the Senior Director of EP&I CEMEA, also based in the Dubai office- Strong collaboration with geography Core Products and EP&I teams- Strong collaboration with Cybersource, Acceptance, Risk, Government Relations and other internal teams- Direct interaction with regional executives, product heads & key clients- External contact with executives with external organizations- This individual is expected to interact effectively with all levels of Visa management and staff- Strong interpersonal skills will be required to address on-going needs of a complex, matrix reporting structure, and multinational organization.- Multicultural sensitivity and interpersonal relationship management skills are essential including the ability to work effectively as part of a teamQualificationsRequired Experience (education, skills - professional/technical/business)Professional- Degree in engineering, business or related field- 8 years’ experience in remote commerce/ payments- Retail banking/financial services sector or card acquiring business experience with demonstrated experience in product development- Proven track record in technical project management and IT service operations- Strong background in risk and fraud pertaining to online security risk and preventive measures.- Proven track record of building partnerships with non-banking clients.- Proven examples of supporting implementation and management of new services or products- Risk Management experience pertaining to online fraud and security in certain industries (airlines, online retail, telecommunications, and Government sectors).- Demonstrable consultative sales experience skills with an employment background in a long sales cycle model- Experience of a matrix organizationTechnical- Deep understanding & exposure to emerging technology, payments, and ecommerce with relevant business development and delivery experience, profitability- Comprehensive conceptual understanding of remote commerce channels, protocols and implementation tools- Knowledge and understanding of banking operations and/ or payment schemes, including products & services, business systems and processes- Proficiency in MS Office suite: Outlook, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint – can prepare executive-level presentations- Significant, senior-level experience and understanding of technical project management and operations- Broad understanding of .Net development framework and Microsoft enterprise technologies in general- Excellent presentation skills- Fluent business English, written & spoken; Language skills in markets served preferredBusiness- Energetic profile, passionate about e-commerce with the ideas, problem solving and tenacity to move more traditional payments onto ecom technology- Adaptability, flexibility and ability to deal with ambiguity in a fast paced and changing environment- Demonstrated experience supporting/leading external and client relationships in support of strategic partnerships; excellent inter-personal skills including cross-cultural sensitivity / adaptability- Demonstrated problem solving skills, ability to negotiate multiple constituencies and manage simultaneous objectives is imperative, particularly while addressing business priorities and constraints- Proven negotiation skills and direction setting- Driven, self-starter, analytical, solution focused, project management skills- Ability to work under deadlines and pressure, as required- Strong verbal and written communication skills
